---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout lang="en" title="Privacy \u2013 Flynn Bertsch">
  <section class="section container">
    <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
    <div class="prose">
      <!--
        IMPORTANT: this is a starter template. Adjust it to the services you actually use
        (additional embeds, contact forms, analytics) and review it regularly.
      -->

      <h2>1. Controller</h2>
      <p>
        Flynn Bertsch<br />
        Musterstra\u00dfe 1<br />
        12345 Musterstadt, Germany<br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:kontakt@example.com">kontakt@example.com</a>
      </p>

      <h2>2. Hosting</h2>
      <p>
        This site is hosted on GitHub Pages (GitHub, Inc., 88 Colin P Kelly Jr St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA).
        When you visit the site, technically necessary data such as your IP address, access time and
        user agent are processed in GitHub server logs. Legal basis: Art. 6 (1) (f) GDPR (legitimate
        interest in providing the site reliably and securely).
        More info: <a href="https://docs.github.com/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-privacy-statement" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub Privacy Statement</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Embedded content (YouTube)</h2>
      <p>
        Some project pages embed videos from YouTube (YouTube LLC, 901 Cherry Ave., San Bruno, CA 94066, USA).
        We use a click-to-load pattern: the YouTube player only loads and contacts YouTube servers after
        you actively click the thumbnail. We additionally use the privacy-friendlier
        <code>youtube-nocookie.com</code> domain.
        More info: <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Cookies</h2>
      <p>This site does not set its own cookies and does not use tracking.</p>

      <h2>5. Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        You have the right to access, rectify, erase, restrict processing of, port, and object to
        the processing of your personal data (Art. 15\u201321 GDPR), as well as the right to lodge a
        complaint with the competent supervisory authority.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Contacting me</h2>
      <p>
        If you contact me by email, the data you send (email address, content of the message) will be
        stored in order to respond to your enquiry. Legal basis: Art. 6 (1) (b) GDPR (pre-contractual
        measures) or (f) GDPR (legitimate interest in replying).
      </p>

      <p><em>Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-GB')}</em></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
